    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>The nearby barred spiral galaxy NGC1097 has a central SMBH with a prominent circumnuclear starburst ring/tight-spiral. It is of considerable interest to identify the source of ISM mass supply outside the starburst ring and at the intersection/connection points of the bars/dust lanes and the ring. There are model predictions for fast mass flows of several hundred kilometers per second along the dark dust lanes parallel to the large-scale bar of NGC1097. With the combined power of high sensitivity and spatial/spectral resolutions of ALMA, we use 12CO(J=2-1) observations as tracers of molecular gas to probe systematic mass flows along dust lanes/bar of NGC1097 to intersect its starburst ring. By ALMA observations, we plan to obtain spatial distribution of CO, line-of-sight ISM gas flow velocity pattern, ISM gas flow speed, and ISM mass flux along dark dust lanes and bar. We would critically examine whether high-speed gas flows exist or not along dust lanes and bar in NGC1097.</prp:abstract>
